# WebRTC and Signaling

## Capture (sender)

- Use `navigator.mediaDevices.getDisplayMedia({ video: true, audio: true })` after a user gesture. Never call without user interaction.
- Stop tracks when ending session: iterate `getTracks()` and call `stop()` to release capture.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD – stop on disconnect
peerConnection.getSenders().forEach(s => s.track?.stop());
```

## PeerConnection

- Add the display stream with `addTrack(track, stream)` (one track per stream). Do not use `addStream` (deprecated).
- Handle ICE candidate gathering and send candidates over the signaling channel; add remote candidates with `addIceCandidate()`.
- Use STUN (e.g. `stun:stun.l.google.com:19302`). Add TURN only if NAT/firewall requires it.

## Signaling

- Exchange only signaling data over WebSocket (offer, answer, ICE candidates). No media over the server.
- Serialize SDP and ICE candidates as JSON. Recreate `RTCSessionDescription` / `RTCIceCandidate` on receive before passing to `setRemoteDescription` / `addIceCandidate`.
- Handle `connectionstatechange` and surface "disconnected" / "failed" to the UI; do not leave the user with a frozen screen.

## Errors

- Catch `getDisplayMedia` rejections (user cancel, permission denied) and show a clear message. Do not swallow errors.
